Some patients may identify with more than one race, or

they may give you a more specific response.

 

Click each button below to learn more.                                           

Self-identifies with More Than

One Race

Your health care organization may allow patients to choose more than one race. If a patient requests more than one race and your system allows it, this is acceptable.

 

As people with more than one racial heritage become aware of opportunities to identify more than one race, this option may become increasingly popular.

 

However, not all persons with parents of different races identify as having more than one race.

Gives a More Specific Response

When answering REAL questions, patients may self-identify with a more specific or granular response that is connected to their country of origin. For example, a patient may state he or she is French, Somalian, or Vietnamese. We will provide you with a job aid you can use to help you choose the appropriate REAL category based upon your patient’s specific response.   Let’s learn more about the specific or granular categories.
